  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "PROJECT MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Collaborate with project engineers and cross-functional trades to coordinate reporting and scheduling, ensuring timely project progress and alignment with overall construction timelines</li><li>Review civil and structural (C&S) drawings for accuracy and completeness to support construction activities, identifying and resolving discrepancies to prevent delays and rework</li><li>Conduct detailed site inspections to monitor construction quality, compliance with design specifications, and safety standards, providing actionable feedback to project teams</li><li>Plan and manage material procurement and logistics to optimize resource availability and minimize project downtime</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Hold a degree in civil engineering recognized by BCA</li><li>Demonstrate a minimum of 8 years of relevant experience in commercial, building, and civil engineering projects</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Exhibit a positive, mature, and self-motivated attitude conducive to autonomous problem-solving and effective team collaboration</li></ul>",
